Not really like Heroes of M&amp;M.  They implicitly said it would be a real-time strategy wargame.  Heroes of Might and Magic was not a real-time combat game, because it was turn based.... altho I loved Heroes III and it was one of the best turn-based strategy games I've ever played. <br>
<br>
So if they say it's real-time strategy... it would be more like Warcraft or Starcraft. A combat strategy game where things are constantly happening at a frantic pace, without a pause. If you blink an eye for 3 seconds, that gives your enemies enough time to send hordes of warriors storming into your cities. <br>
